ZCZC EE45
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 172300 UTC
AT THE START OF THE PERIOD AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE IS
EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER THE CENTRAL BRITISH ISLES. THREE
SEPARATE LOWS ARE EXP TO SURROUND THIS SYSTEM. ONE
LOCATED CLOSE TO THE SW OF FITZROY ONE MIDWAY BETWEEN
GREENLAND AND ICELAND AND A THIRD LOCATED OVER FINLAND.
DURING WEDNESDAY THE HIGH IS EXP TO BECOME STRETCHED AND
MAY WELL SPLIT INTO TWO SEPARATE CENTRES ONE IN THE MID-
ATLANTIC AND ONE OVER THE CONTINENT. THE LOW TO THE S-W
IS LIKELY TO DRIFT A LITTLE NWARDS WHILE THE OTHER TWO
LOWS BECOME WEAK FEATURES. BY FRIDAY THE HIGH IN THE MID-
ATLANTIC IS EXP TO BECOME AN INTENSE FEATURE AND THIS
WILL MAINTAIN THE LARGELY BLOCKED PATTER WE HAVE SEEN
OVER THE PAST FEW WEEKS. EARLY IN THE PERIOD STRG WINDS
ARE LIKELY ACROSS MUCH OF NITON. GRADUALLY WINDS ACROSS
THE S SHOULD MOD BECMG CONFINED TO SOLE AND SHANNON BY
